@startuml
title MicroMeet - Activity Diagram (Respond to Join Request - Accept/Decline)

start
:1. User opens Join Request response screen;
:2. User selects Accept or Decline;
:3. User submits response;
:4. System validates response;

if (Response valid?) then (Yes)
  :5. System loads meetup;
  if (Choice = Accept?) then (Yes)
    :6. System checks capacity;
    if (Capacity available?) then (Yes)
      :7. System sets participation status = ACCEPTED;
      :8. System saves updated meetup/roster;
      :9. System notifies host and user;
      :10. Show updated status;
    else (No)
      :11. Show "Meetup full" error;
    endif
  else (Decline)
    :12. System sets participation status = DECLINED;
    :13. System saves updated meetup/roster;
    :14. System notifies host;
    :15. Show updated status;
  endif
else (No)
  :16. Show validation errors;
endif

stop

legend bottom
Steps mapping (numbers match actions):
1 Open join response screen
2 Choose accept/decline
3 Submit response
4 Validate response
5 Load meetup
6 Check capacity (accept)
7 Set status accepted
8 Save roster
9 Notify host/user
10 Show updated status
11 Meetup full error
12 Set status declined
13 Save roster
14 Notify host
15 Show updated status
16 Validation errors
endlegend

@enduml